  "text": "This theorem allows us to validate Eqn. 8, and to explain the aspect of a 2D slice of noise from the power spectrum of the 3D solid noise (e.g., in Fig. 4 ). Note that, although the Fourier Slice Theorem as used by [CITATION_1] provides the basic intuition, this theorem is more general and more complete. For example, the proof of this theorem explains why the slicing plane Π does not have to go through the origin, which is not explained by the Fourier Slice Theorem alone. We believe this theorem might have applications beyond noise (e.g., 3D solid texture extrapolation from 2D exemplar slices).",
